  'summary': "Alphabet reports Q1 revenue of $69.8bn, beating analyst predictions and marking a 3% YoY increase. The company's cloud business recorded its first profit, and Alphabet announced a $70bn stock buyback, boosting shares by nearly 3% in after-hours trading. CEO Sundar Pichai emphasized the focus on AI and search capabilities in the company's future plans.",
