    "summary": "Kansas has enacted one of the most restrictive transgender bathroom bills in U.S. history. Republican legislators overrode Democratic Governor Laura Kelly's veto of the measure, which defines sex as an \"individual\u2019s biological sex, either male or female, at birth.\" The new law also legally defines women and men based on their biological reproductive systems and applies to school restrooms, locker rooms, prisons, domestic violence shelters and rape crisis centers. Supporters argue that such legislation is needed to prevent transgender women from sharing facilities with cisgender women and girls, while opponents criticize the law for being too broad and difficult to enforce. Some LGBTQ activists argue that the measure could write transgender people out of state law. TL;DR: Kansas enacts one of the most sweeping and restrictive transgender bathroom bills in US history.",
