    "content": "Scientists studying data from China's Zhurong rover have for the first time found cracked layers on tiny Martian dunes, which imply the Red Planet was a salt-rich watery world as recently as 400,000 \u2026 [+4826 chars]",
    "summary": "Scientists studying data from China's Zhurong rover have discovered cracked layers on miniature Martian dunes that imply the Red Planet was a salt-rich watery world as recently as 400,000 years ago. The data suggests that Martian water played a major role in creating the dunes' intriguing surface features. The rover used a laser-induced breakdown spectrometer to analyse sand grains and found hydrated minerals that formed in the presence of water at low latitudes in the late Amazonian era on Mars, which scientists previously thought was bone-dry. The findings indicate that future missions to Mars could search for microbial life forms that might be able to tolerate salts or brines.",
